HEADWORD: Prefatory
<hw>Pref"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to, or
of the nature of, a preface; introductory to a book, essay, or
discourse; <as>as, <ex>prefatory</ex> remarks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That <qex>prefatory</qex> addition to the Creed.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prefect</ent>⟦br⟧
